  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rebuild Flooded Burma Refugee Camp Recovery Centre</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Thai floods of 2011 started in the north of Thailand, where DARE Network works in 5 Burmese Refugee camps on the Thai/Burma Border.  During this rainy season our DARE Centre buildings were badly damaged. We have already rebuilt 1 Centre but need your help with 4 more. DARE (Drug and Alcohol Recovery and Education) Network provides highly successful community-based prevention education and non-medical culturally appropriate addiction treatment to the communities of 150,000 Burmese Refugees.</narrative>
  </description>
